{"overview":"This piece is cast in a gentle ternary form anchored in the remote, veiled key of G-flat major, distinguished above all by its extraordinarily bold network of enharmonic modulations—most strikingly the reinterpretation of a German augmented sixth chord as a diminished seventh to pivot through E minor and back—which lend the pastoral, arpeggiated texture a sense of dreamlike harmonic dissolution and reawakening.","cross_piece_tags":["ternary","nocturne","lyrical","meditative","arpeggiated_bass","enharmonic_modulation","chromatic_mediant","modal_mixture"]}
